If we take a decorated member function and try to call it on an object, the wrapped member function is missing its `__name__`, `__module__`, etc. Should those attributes be available on `wrapped`?

```python
import wrapt

@wrapt.decorator
def my_decorator(wrapped, instance, args, kwargs):
    print wrapped.__name__, wrapped.__module__
    return wrapped(*args, **kwargs)

class MyClass(object):
    @my_decorator
    def my_func(self):
        pass

o = MyClass()
o.my_func()  # works

method = MyClass.my_func
method(o)  # crashes with AttributeError: 'functools.partial' object has no attribute '__name__'
```

