Currently, we have (with some bits cut out)

```
message TensorShapeProto {
  ...
  repeated Dimension dim = 1;
}

message TypeProto {
  message Tensor {
    ...
    optional TensorShapeProto shape = 2;
  }
  ...
}
```

In theory, we can represent "no shape information" by having `has_shape()` be false, and we can represent "scalar" as "`has_shape()` is true, and `dim_size()` is zero".

However, the C++ protobuf api doesn't distinguish between these two cases (it can be done in python, for example see https://gist.github.com/anderspapitto/f772b697ced651ff3aefba0dbcab02ee)

So we may need to add an additional field to the protobuf definitions to represent "no shape information"
